args: I was wondering where you'd\ndisappeared to.
Sorry, I just had to hear the waves one\nmore time before heading home.
It's sad to think we likely won't be back\nhere again anytime soon.
Anyway, did you need me for something?
I came to give you this.\nIt's tropical fruit juice, fresh squeezed.
Nina taught me how to make it.
It's made from fruits local to this area.
Oh, wow! Let me give it a try.
Mmm... It's sweet, but also a bit tangy?\nI think I could drink this all day.
Er, sorry I drank so much.
Would you like some more?\nI have plenty.
I sort of...drank it all at once...
Well, you clearly like it.\nHold on a moment.
Here you are. This should last you a while\nlonger, at least.
Wait, a whole bottle?! Are you sure there's\nenough left for everyone else?
Oh, they have more than enough.
I made you a separate batch to begin with.
To thank you for coaxing me out from\nunder my umbrella.
I had a splendid day, all thanks to you.
There's no need to thank me.\nI had a lot of fun too.
Oh, but there is. Without your company,\nI would have done naught but stare at\nthe sea till day's end.
All the while telling myself it was due\nto the heat, or my duty as a retainer...
But the truth, in fact, is that I wished\nto enjoy myself as much as the others.
Then all those things you said earlier...
Nothing more than thinly veiled lies, yes.

I wanted to throw my cares away,
but the thought of actually doing
so froze me solid. Which is ironic,
given the heat.
I made those excuses to avoid facing\nmy fear.
When you spend so much of your life\nnot doing something, it can be hard to\nembrace it so suddenly.
I just couldn't imagine myself frolicking\non the beach, I suppose.
Well, you HAVE been in the forest a\nlong time. I can see how that would\nbe hard.
I'm very glad I was able to overcome\nthat unease.
And I would never have done so\nwithout you.
All that matters to me is that you\nenjoyed yourself.
But I'd forgotten just how quickly a\nday can speed by when you leave\nyour worries behind.
I feel sad that it's almost time to leave.
...Would you mind if I joined you?
I would like to listen to the waves as well.
The twinkle of the stars in the water\nis dazzling.
A fitting end to such a dream of a day.
I see what you mean; once we return to\nthe Halidom, our fight will begin anew.
I am afraid there are still many battles\nyet to be fought.
But I believe the memories we made today\nwill fuel our efforts.
That's a pretty thought, Your Highness,\nbut I doubt we'll have the luxury.
We will, once peace has been restored\nto this land.
And that means next time, we'll have\neven MORE fun!
Today is more than a dream.\nIt's the very future we're fighting for!
There aren't many who can speak with\nsuch sincerity about their goals.
And I shall do all in my power to see\nyou realize them.
Perhaps then we can add to these seaside\nmemories each year.
Let's come back here and have fun again\none day!
